               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols. 3ra-5rb)&#xD; II)
                     Maṣḥafa lǝdätu la-ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot “Book of the Genealogy of ʾabuna Takla
                     Haymanot” (fols. 5rb-6va)&#xD; - Genealogy of Takla Hāymānot (fols.
                     5rb-6va)&#xD; III) Gadla Takla Hāymānot “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols.
                     7ra-104va)&#xD; - Introduction (fols. 7ra-10vb)&#xD; - Gadla Takla Hāymānot
                     “Vita of Takla Haymanot” (fols. 10vb-104va)&#xD; IV) Taʾāmra Takla Hāymānot
                     “Miracles of Takla Haymanot”: 19 miracles (fols. 105ra-115vb)&#xD; V) Gadla
                     ʾEwosṭatewos “Vita of ʾEwosṭatewos” (fols. 116ra-140vb)&#xD; VI) Taʾāmra
                     ʾEwosṭatewos “Miracles of ʾEwosṭatewos”: 11 miracles (fols. 141ra-149rb)&#xD;
                     &#xD; Additiones 1-4.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The text of the Vita of Takla Hāymānot has some characteristics of the
                        so-called "Ḥayq recension" of Gadla Takla Hāymānot. Cp. Mss. EMML n<locus target="#1834">1834</locus> (EMML V, 310-14); BN, Éth. 342 (GrébGriaule
                        II, 18-20), Ṭānāsee 162 (SixTana III, 202-06). For a (rough) French
                        translation of the text s. J. DUCHESNE-FOURNET, Mission en Éthiopie, 1<ref type="mss" corresp="ES901190">901-190</ref>3, vol. 1, Paris 1908,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES340431">340-431</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- The name of the original donor, Dǝmyanos, is incorporated into the
                        ḥaräg <locus target="#105r">105r</locus>.</note>
                     <note>- The name of the church to which the book was originally (?) donated is
                        written in red inside an ornamental band, <locus target="#105r">105r</locus>: Wägʷalḥǝṭ/Wänlḥǝṭ (?).</note>
                  </msItem>
